title: Emergency Service Zones, Cass County ND
name: Emergency Service Zones, Cass County ND
description:
Coverage of Cass County Emergency Service Zones (ESN).

This data consists of an ArcSDE feature class of Emergency Service Zones for Cass County, North Dakota. The data originates from the 9-1-1 Coordinator for Cass County based on coverage agreements with the various first responders or which was established by a statute, such as Fire Districts and Law Enforcement. The various boundaries within the county comprise the three main responders for each separate ESN (Emergency Service Number) zone in the telephone dataset maintained by Intrado under contract with QWEST. The three responders identified in each zone are Fire, Medical and Law Enforcement. A new ESN is required whenever any one of the three main responders changes for a particular area or zone. This is necessary so that an enhanced E-9-1-1 call can be identified when it comes into a Public Safety Answering Point as to the appropriate first responder(s) to dispatch on the incident. In the future this will also include a locator field (ALI) by lat/long or similar identifier attached to each E-9-1-1 call.
